        "designer": "Keith Foster",
        "description": "The Harvester is a golf club located in Rhodes, Iowa. It is known for its unique design and challenging layout. The course was designed by Keith Foster and opened in 2005. Home to the Iowa State Mens and Womans golf team, it postures itself as a national golf destination and future USGA site.",
        "personal_anecdote": "There is nothing like The Harvester in the state of Iowa. It is a true championship course: long, fast, firm, and mean. Taking inspiration from the best courses in the world, it offers a unique challenge. If you want to find out what it's like to play in Major Championship conditions, drive 45 minutes northeast of Des Moines and bring your wallet.",
